               3.23. City of Rohnert Park Transactions and Use Tax</h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">7287.27.</h6> (a) Notwithstanding any other law, the City of Rohnert Park, by ordinance, may impose a transactions and use tax for general or specific purposes at a rate of no more than 0.75 percent that would, in combination with all taxes imposed in accordance with Part 1.6 (commencing with Section 7251), exceed the limit established in Section 7251.1, if all of the following requirements are met:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The city council of the City of Rohnert Park adopts an ordinance proposing the transactions and use tax by the applicable voting approval requirement.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The ordinance proposing the transactions and use tax is submitted
